the rhyme between Betelgeuse and

40:44.620 --> 40:48.540
Proust and for the lady of a physicist I was kind of tickled by that rhyme.

40:49.400 --> 40:52.800
But science fiction poetry is just a gimmick that people can use

40:52.800 --> 40:56.400
and get into magazines. Do you think that's something that's real

40:56.400 --> 40:58.100
and maybe will become more important?

40:59.940 --> 41:04.200
Well I've always felt that it was possible to write poetry about anything

41:04.200 --> 41:07.380
so that it seems to me entirely possible and viable

41:07.380 --> 41:11.180
and legitimate to write poetry about

41:13.740 --> 41:15.020
speculative subjects

41:15.020 --> 41:19.240
or subjects that use science in one way or another.

41:19.840 --> 41:22.920
Whether it's a gimmick on the part of the people who are writing it

41:22.920 --> 41:27.040
to get into the magazines I have no idea. I'm sure that the science fiction magazines

41:27.040 --> 41:30.740
could not publish any other type of poetry however

41:31.420 --> 41:34.940
but poetry that deals with the speculative subject

41:34.940 --> 41:38.680
or with science in some way or another.

